CPV DNA loads in vaccines and field samples were calculated in parallel by the developed type2/variants MGB probe assay and by the TaqMan assay established previously (Decaro et al., 2005c). As shown in Fig. 3
, the two assays were found to correlate well over the shared 8 log10 dynamic ranges, calculating similar DNA titres for the same samples. In contrast, a poor correlation was found between the vaccine titres reported by manufacturers and expressed by CCID50 and the DNA copy numbers calculated by the MGB probe assay (Table 3
).
